caption: Traditional and fresh....while on the pricier side, EVERYTHING is delicious & worth it, everytime.

They forgot to pack my tzatziki and hummus, no big deal. Except when I called to ask about it the waitress (Christy or Christine) was insanely rude - like, I just sat there on the phone in shock. She told me “Ok you have all these complaints! Do you want me to pay for it OUT OF MY OWN POCKET?!!!” Huh? I know it’s hard to be in the service industry, now more than ever, but you made a mistake - just send over my missing food that I paid for or refund it or something and it’s all good. Why are we getting crazy? So for $15 plus tax, tip and fees I got 8 grilled chicken nuggets and a few hot cucumber slices.
Amazing food!

Uber eats had a buy one get one promotion and I wanted greek food.  Have to say the falafel is some of the best I have ever had, when you bite into them and see the center they aren’t just packed full of chickpea and wow they reqlly taste fresh. Delicious!  The tzatziki isn’t watery thin garbage, is has a thick consistency like sour cream and is packed with flavor. I’m very happy with the food. Will order from them again.
Great food

I got to say the food here is really good! I'm armenian so when I'm telling u the food is good the food is great!! I got the chicken plate the rice was very good not dry and the chicken was juicy. The staff was super friendly also the place was super clean. I'm glad to be the first person to also leave a google here good job guys keep it up.

The foods are great, especially pork souvlaki and falafel.

Underhill Greek Eatery is a local go-to for my wife and me. Great food every time. We're both big fans of the moussaka. The soups and apps are excellent, too. Very pleased to have this restaurant in the neighborhood!
Great restaurant. It’s my go-to Greek in BK

i ordered delivery and got the lamb burger bc it had such rave reviews on here! it was tasty, the crispy cheese is so yummy, the pickles, dressing, onions- all together it was so complimentary and delicious. 4 stars only bc while it was delicious, i felt my burger was just a bit overcooked. other than that, it’s a thumbs up from me! oh! and they included a complimentary dessert that was tasty as well.
Delicious food, fresh delivery and great service!
Don’t usually leave reviews but ordered uber eats from here and they threw in an extra dessert for the holidays! Really made my day and the food we ordered was excellent!
Great food and great service!

Holy moly!! The lamb burger is everything I could want it to be and more.  The fantastic twist with the cheese was an amazing surprise. I've been living in this neighborhood for way to long without ever trying this place.  I will most certainly be back! We could feel the love and care in all the preparation and even the delivery service. See you soon Underhill Eatery!
Really delicious food that tastes fresh and homemade - would definitely order again!

I stopped by this establishment today on the way home from work. They have the best the tastiest lamb gyro I ever had. My wife and I were extremely happy with our food!! 5 STARS!!

Delicious and so reasonably priced! A great new addition to Prospect Heights. Try the grilled octopus (so tender, cooked perfectly, light), zucchini croquettes are my favorite with a side of tzatziki. The traditional Cretan Dakos salad with barely rusk, feta and tomatoes was exceptional. The restaurant bar had a wide range of perfectly crafted wines (many imported from the motherland, aka Greece itself. I would recommend the white Santorini.  The atmosphere is cozy yet sophisticated. It's Modern Greek food at its finest.
Very tasty food and speedy delivery!
Love their food! Tasty, healthy, and fast!
Soooo delicious! And the staff is very sweet. Would definitely recommend this place to anyone in the area looking for really good Greek food.

We were disappointed because we were excited to order more then that wanting support the community. But the food was mediocre at best. Ordered: the grill salmon + the gyro platter w/salad. I must say the customer service was top notch which let's face it --really just Google. Even still the food ---could have been from anywhere there was nothing authentically Greek about it not the lamb, salmon, hummus, or tzatziki sauce. Sad faced because I absolutely love Greek food. But we didn't get it here.
Our takeout order arrived in no time and it was hot, tasty and correct. Great service!!
Really delicious dishes, great value, and big portions! Loved the spanakopita, falafel, grilled halloumi, and greek salad! The free order of baklava was super yummy as well.
Such a hidden gem in the neighborhood! More people need to know about this place. Great fresh salads, hot pita w/ delicious mezzes, and great grilled chicken, lamb and shrimp. This place is my fav

This is the best value in the entire neighborhood with a very wide variety. Everything is great here: classic greek dishes that feature octopus and shrimp to their burgers. You can’t go wrong here, and they have a very good beer/wine list

It is so good with crispy cheese on the bottom. Mmm. The spanikopita was a bit soggy but flavor is great. We love this spot.

One recommendation is to ask them to wrap the container with the lemon chicken in foil or use a tighter container because most of the juices/sauce spilled out into the bag. They gave us 1 free baklava dessert which was nice and thanked us for the order. Great place!
My go-to for Greek takeout. Great food, friendly staff, and always ready quick!
Got takeout for the first time, great experience! Everything was delicious and we will be back!
Always delicious and so FRESH. I’ve tried the Greek salad, burger, chicken souvlaki, lamb keftedes, the dips, and the baklava. A+ every time.
Have only ever ordered takeout. Food is ready quickly and is very fresh with large portions. Halloumi pita is delicious and flavorful.
Incredible meal via Uber Eats. Lamb burger, moussaka, traditional Greek salad all yummy.
Great!

This place is so, so good! I dropped in this evening with my partner for dinner and Nicole behind the bar was very personable and had great recommendations. The ambiance is so cute with nice lighting and great greek music. We ate at the bar, but there was a good amount of seating. It was surprisingly full for a Tuesday night! (good sign) The menu had an appropriate amount of options, including some vegetarian-friendly ones. Grape leaves were the bomb dot com. I loved the Chicken Bifteki, which was essentially a chicken burger patty served with salad, tzatziki, fries, and warm pita. The burger had really nice grill marks on it and almost tasted like it was cooked on a wood fire. My partner got the halloumi platter which was served with essentially the same things but had cheese in lieu of the chicken patty. It was also delicious. To end it all, we had baklava. It was perfectly sweetened, great layering, and just the right amount of rosewater so it didn't overwhelm or overpower. Despite all the options this area of Brooklyn has to offer, we will definitely come back and eat here again.
Great local spot

We had the soup special and the soup completely lacked flavor. The meatball dish was also meh it drowned in tomato sauce and felt very heavy. The dishes took a while to come out and the general vibe at the restaurant seemed like the waitresses were having hard time keeping up with the orders. I love greek food but I probably won’t go here again.
I love going to this place, the staff is very friendly and the food is really good as well! I definitely recommend this place for very nice Greek food or burgers too.
Great meal and service! Octopus, ribeye, and shrimp dishes were all phenomenal. Free baklava for dessert was a really nice touch. Looking forward to coming back and trying more!

The folks there were very friendly and accommodating!! Oh, as we were standing out front deciding whether to eat there or not a number of policemen passing by said it was the place to try!! What a surprise- amazing Greek / American eatery in what looks like a British style pub. Get the pork ribs, crispy sprouts, octopus.. can’t miss. Great outdoor seats too.

Delicious food and great ambiance. Staff is friendly and upbeat. Excited to eat here again.

Perfect addition to the Prospect heights neighborhood !!  A refined Greek fusion cafe bar restaurant. Festive environment with a cool bar, popular beer/wine selections .....  and really really good food  !!!  This family owned establishment offers an extremely awesome mixed menu, including tasty bar comfort food, traditional Greek dishes and creative modern Greek-American fusions.  ** FYI - They have their own family style house cooked pita which is incredibly fresh and tasty **  *** FYII - If your just looking for good bar comfort food - They have amazing burgers, pizza .. and some fire Greek cheese fries !  Look below for all my personal faves :  Sesame and Honey Saganaki !! - Fried kefalograviera cheese with honey comb, tahini, herb puree, sesame seeds, and fresh house cooked pita .  Underhill Lamb Burger ( a banging Greek-American burger !! )  - Topped with graviera cheese, bacon onion jam, bacon aioli, and dill pickles - with a side of french fries  Dakos Salad !  -  A salad broken down to the bare essentials with barley rusk, tomatoes, onions, feta, parsley and extra virgin olive oil.  Underhill Pizza ( The Perfect Greek-American Pizza Fusion !! ) - Mushrooms, Goat cheese, bacon, chili, basil pesto.  Octopus - (The go to Greek appetizer !! ) Fresh grilled octopus with lemon herb vinaigrette.  Grilled Pork Rib -  Pork rib topped with pickle red onions, herb salad, and grilled lemon with side of tzatziki

Underhill Brooklyn is a such an great new spot in Brooklyn! With great tasting authentic Greek food, fun upbeat Greek music and a friendly staff, this place is sure to be a hit. I had the kale salad which was tasty and fresh and the spanakopita which was homemade and delicious. I would highly recommend this place to anyone looking for a taste of Greece in Brooklyn.

Excellent food. Underhill pizza is delicious. Mushrooms, bacon, peppers, pesto - layers of flavor! Beets with feta very good. Zucchini cheese balls were very creamy and delicious. Excellent meal.

My husband and I found this place a month ago and have already been back many times! The food here is so good - fresh and flavorful. The menu is great - try the dips (eggplant, tzaziki and tomato feta!), lamb keftedes, Greek salad and salmon. The slouvaki is also a solid staple. Hope this place is here for many more meals to come!
This has to be my new favorite local spot.

Been here several times since they've opened, since I live down the street. The food is excellent! The atmosphere is great for any occasion be it dinner with friends, a quick bite and a beer at the bar, or date night.  The kitchen takes Greek staples and gives them a fresh, modern twist that compliments it very well. The fried cheese with honey is one of my favorite apps along with the octopus. Mains you can't go wrong with the pork ribs, souvlaki, or the shrimp saganaki.  If you live in the neighborhood or close by you certainly need to try it! They also just started doing brunch as well.

I had the pork ribs and they were literally falling off the bone delicious! Came with a group of friends and everyone loved their food.  Especially the lamb burgers and spanakopita. The service was excellent and everyone is so sweet. Family run place and super clean. Can't wait to come back!
